import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    data['year'] = data['year'].dt.year

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='people', hue='sex', data=data, palette='viridis', ci=None)
    plt.title('What is the trend of population growth over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Population')
    plt.legend(title='Sex', labels=['Male', 'Female'])
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='age', bins=20, kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['age'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['age'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of age in the population data?", wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    gender_counts = data['sex'].value_counts().reset_index()
    gender_counts.columns = ['sex', 'count']
    gender_counts['sex'] = gender_counts['sex'].replace({1: 'Male', 2: 'Female'})

    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
    ax = sns.barplot(x='sex', y='count', data=gender_counts, palette='viridis')
    plt.title('What is the gender distribution in the population data?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Gender')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    ax.legend(title='Gender', labels=['Male', 'Female'], loc='upper right')

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
